Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
loadSpecialRoute(25.10)                                loadSpecialRoute(25.10)

Name
       loadSpecialRoute  -  Loads  the spr file generated through the saveSpe-
       cialRoute command

Syntax
        loadSpecialRoute

       [-help]

       <filename>

       Loads the spr file generated through the saveSpecialRoute  command.  It
       also clears all special routes and loads the specified spr file. If the
       spr files are loaded incrementally, the addSpecialRoute command must be
       used. If the specified filename is compressed (with the .gz extension),
       the file is read in directly.

Parameters
       -help  Prints  a  brief  description that includes the type and default
              information for each loadSpecialRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and  all  its  parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man loadSpecialRoute

       <filename>
              Specifies  the  name of the file that contains special route in-
              formation, to be used as input for the design.

Related Information
              * addSpecialRoute

              * saveSpecialRoute

              * Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

